食物質素太差，價錢有點不合理，所謂自家制食品大部份在外攞回當自家制。有㸃！

好一般，建議去另一間

result.name: Lam Tsuen Wishing Tree

reviews.text: Peaceful walk on weekday. Spectacular view behind the restroom building. Nice chat with local elderly. Convenient traffic. But aware of mosquitoes.

First time visit after pass by and heard from news so many time. The actual wishing is now done on a fake tree but there wasn't really a "The Tree" it's been change quite many times mainly due to the damaging activities that is the wishing. So it probably good idea now it's done on a non living tree.

A meaningful place for local people. It has a big tree that allows people throwing the lucky pack onto it to show the wish that want to come true. There is also a big drum that you have to knock before throwing your wish on the tree as you need to acknowledge the goddess. Beautiful and nice cultural place to go when visiting Hong Kong.
Colorful and festive, but also very crowded and loud. Take your pick! Either way, it's a cultural experience that is worth sampling, or diving headlong into.

The original wishing tree is no longer accessible. Now delegated to paying an old lady to do rituals for you. 

Not particularly worth going to if you're far away. Still good to get some good luck
